history.content: Taking 120 and 105 is a very good idea: between the two, you will get a great broad overview of EE, & will be able to decide in what area you want to focus on (systems & signals (very general), device physics, analog circuits).  120 is also fairly useful for 105 (and necessary for harder circuit classes/knowledge) as basic pole/zero/stability concepts are directly applicable to circuit design.  Expect about 10hrs/week for both.  As for 106a, it's a relatively low workload/difficulty class. So yes, I think it's a great schedule.

Hi all,

I'm planning on taking EE120 and 106a next semester, but am also considering tacking on 105 to this schedule. I'll be taking CS195 and another, trivial breadth. 

Would taking these 3 techs at the same time be doable? I've heard that EE105's workload was cut down significantly starting Fall 2016 -- has this held up for Spring 17? 

I know there have been some posts already regarding 105 but I'm hoping for someone who took 105 in the spring to comment. Also, how is Ming Wu as a professor as they'll be teaching in the Fall.

Thanks!
